  Line 627:             "output": "<path>/home/mark/sandbox/personal/pr-review-chatbot/openspec/changes/update-pr-review-summary-ui-readability/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: ## Why\n2: \n3: The PR Summary tab currently renders dense, low-hierarchy content that is difficult to scan quickly during review. Improving readability now reduces reviewer fatigue and helps users identify key changes faster without changing the underlying summary generation flow.\n4: \n5: ## What Changes\n6: \n7: - Update PR Summary tab display to render generated content in discrete panels using the same container styling pattern as the Comments and Reviews panes.\n8: - Split summary output into an `Orientation` panel and one panel per `Focus Area` item when present.\n9: - Apply title color accents to improve scanability: blue for `Orientation` and yellow for each `Focus Area` panel title.\n10: - Preserve existing summary generation flow, prompt/config behavior, caching/rate-limiting, and fallback-state behavior.\n11: \n12: ## Capabilities\n13: \n14: ### New Capabilities\n15: \n16: - None.\n17: \n18: ### Modified Capabilities\n19: \n20: - `pr-review-summary`: Update summary tab presentation requirements to enforce readable hierarchy, spacing, and markdown rendering behavior across summary states.\n21: \n22: ## Impact\n23: \n24: - Affected UI: `src/components/PRViewer.tsx` summary tab rendering and related style definitions.\n25: - Potentially affected tests: summary tab component tests and visual-state assertions.\n26: - No API contract changes, backend changes, or dependency additions expected.\n\n(End of file - total 26 lines)\n</content>",
